From: orange <root@localhost>
Subject: [PATCH] Allow login screen to open temporary reauthentication channels

The login screen greeter calls OpenReauthenticationChannel when a user
clicks their name.  When no session exists for that user (first login),
the daemon returned ACCESS_DENIED.  The greeter JS is supposed to catch
that and fall back to GetUserVerifier, but due to a bug in libgdm
(gdm_client_get_user_verifier returns a stale cached proxy whose
underlying GDBusConnection was already torn down by run_dispose()), the
fallback path fails with "The connection is closed".

Remove the login-screen error block so the code falls through to
open_temporary_reauthentication_channel(), which is designed to handle
exactly this case (session == NULL).  This makes first-time login work
without triggering the stale-proxy fallback path.
---
 daemon/gdm-manager.c | 8 --------
 1 file changed, 8 deletions(-)

diff --git a/daemon/gdm-manager.c b/daemon/gdm-manager.c
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/daemon/gdm-manager.c
+++ b/daemon/gdm-manager.c
@@ -1219,14 +1219,6 @@ gdm_manager_handle_open_reauthentication_channel (GdmDBusManager        *manage
                         g_debug("GdmManager: user session is frozen; using temporary reauthentication channel");
                 }
-        } else if (is_login_screen) {
-                g_dbus_method_invocation_return_error_literal (invocation,
-                                                               G_DBUS_ERROR,
-                                                               G_DBUS_ERROR_ACCESS_DENIED,
-                                                               "Login screen only allowed to open reauthentication channels for running sessions");
-                return TRUE;
-        }
-
         address = open_temporary_reauthentication_channel (self,
                                                            is_login_screen? session : NULL,
                                                            seat_id,
